T1  - A Primal Method for Minimal Cost Flows with Applications to the Assignment and Transportation Problems
AU  - Klein, Morton
Y1  - 1967/11/01
PY  - 1967
DA  - 1967/11/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.14.3.205
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.14.3.205
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 205
EP  - 220
VL  - 14
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A simple procedure is given for solving minimal cost flow problems in which feasible flows are maintained throughout. It specializes to give primal algorithms for the assignment and transportation problems. Convex cost problems can also be handled.
AB  - A simple procedure is given for solving minimal cost flow problems in which feasible flows are maintained throughout. It specializes to give primal algorithms for the assignment and transportation problems. Convex cost problems can also be handled.
